 1329   
 1330   static int32_T div_s32_floor(int32_T numerator, int32_T denominator)
 1331   {
 1332     int32_T quotient;
 1333     uint32_T absNumerator;
 1334     uint32_T absDenominator;
 1335     int32_T quotientNeedsNegation;
 1336     uint32_T tempAbsQuotient;
 1337     if (denominator == 0) {
 1338       if (numerator >= 0) {
 1339         quotient = MAX_int32_T;
 1340       } else {
 1341         quotient = MIN_int32_T;
 1342       }
 1343   
 1344       emlrtDivisionByZeroErrorR2012b(0, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1345     } else {
 1346       if (numerator >= 0) {
 1347         absNumerator = (uint32_T)numerator;
 1348       } else {
 1349         absNumerator = (uint32_T)-numerator;
 1350       }
 1351   
 1352       if (denominator >= 0) {
 1353         absDenominator = (uint32_T)denominator;
 1354       } else {
 1355         absDenominator = (uint32_T)-denominator;
 1356       }
 1357   
 1358       quotientNeedsNegation = ((numerator < 0) != (denominator < 0));
 1359       tempAbsQuotient = absNumerator / absDenominator;
 1360       if ((uint32_T)quotientNeedsNegation) {
 1361         absNumerator %= absDenominator;
 1362         if (absNumerator > (uint32_T)0) {
 1363           tempAbsQuotient++;
 1364         }
 1365       }
 1366   
 1367       if ((uint32_T)quotientNeedsNegation) {
 1368         quotient = -(int32_T)tempAbsQuotient;
 1369       } else {
 1370         quotient = (int32_T)tempAbsQuotient;
 1371       }
 1372     }
 1373   
 1374     return quotient;
 1375   }

 1377   static void eml_li_find(const emxArray_boolean_T *x, emxArray_int32_T *y)
 1378   {
 1379     int32_T k;
 1380     boolean_T overflow;
 1381     int32_T i;
 1382     const mxArray *b_y;
 1383     const mxArray *m4;
 1384     int32_T j;
 1385     emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&uc_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1386     k = 0;
 1387     emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&xc_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1388     if (1 > x->size[1]) {
 1389       overflow = FALSE;
 1390     } else {
 1391       overflow = (x->size[1] > 2147483646);
 1392     }
 1393   
 1394     if (overflow) {
 1395       emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&jb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1396       check_forloop_overflow_error(TRUE);
 1397       emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&jb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1398     }
 1399   
 1400     emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&xc_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1401     for (i = 1; i <= x->size[1]; i++) {
 1402       if (x->data[i - 1]) {
 1403         k++;
 1404       }
 1405     }
 1406   
 1407     emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&uc_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1408     if (k <= x->size[1]) {
 1409     } else {
 1410       emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&vc_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1411       b_y = NULL;
 1412       m4 = mxCreateString("Assertion failed.");
 1413       emlrtAssign(&b_y, m4);
 1414       error(b_y, &s_emlrtMCI);
 1415       emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&vc_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1416     }
 1417   
 1418     j = y->size[0] * y->size[1];
 1419     y->size[0] = 1;
 1420     y->size[1] = k;
 1421     emxEnsureCapacity((emxArray__common *)y, j, (int32_T)sizeof(int32_T),
 1422                       &fb_emlrtRTEI);
 1423     j = 0;
 1424     emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&wc_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1425     if (1 > x->size[1]) {
 1426       overflow = FALSE;
 1427     } else {
 1428       overflow = (x->size[1] > 2147483646);
 1429     }
 1430   
 1431     if (overflow) {
 1432       emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&jb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1433       check_forloop_overflow_error(TRUE);
 1434       emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&jb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1435     }
 1436   
 1437     emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&wc_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1438     for (i = 1; i <= x->size[1]; i++) {
 1439       if (x->data[i - 1]) {
 1440         y->data[j] = i;
 1441         j++;
 1442       }
 1443     }
 1444   }

 1446   static void eml_sort_idx(const emxArray_real_T *x, emxArray_int32_T *idx)
 1447   {
 1448     uint32_T uv1[2];
 1449     int32_T k;
 1450     boolean_T overflow;
 1451     emxArray_int32_T *idx0;
 1452     int32_T i;
 1453     int32_T i2;
 1454     int32_T j;
 1455     int32_T pEnd;
 1456     int32_T p;
 1457     int32_T q;
 1458     int32_T qEnd;
 1459     int32_T kEnd;
 1460     emlrtHeapReferenceStackEnterFcnR2012b(emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1461     for (k = 0; k < 2; k++) {
 1462       uv1[k] = (uint32_T)x->size[k];
 1463     }
 1464   
 1465     k = idx->size[0] * idx->size[1];
 1466     idx->size[0] = 1;
 1467     idx->size[1] = (int32_T)uv1[1];
 1468     emxEnsureCapacity((emxArray__common *)idx, k, (int32_T)sizeof(int32_T),
 1469                       &n_emlrtRTEI);
 1470     if (x->size[1] == 0) {
 1471       emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&fb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1472       emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&fb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1473     } else {
 1474       emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&gb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1475       overflow = (x->size[1] > 2147483646);
 1476       if (overflow) {
 1477         emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&jb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1478         check_forloop_overflow_error(TRUE);
 1479         emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&jb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1480       }
 1481   
 1482       emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&gb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1483       for (k = 1; k <= x->size[1]; k++) {
 1484         idx->data[k - 1] = k;
 1485       }
 1486   
 1487       emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&hb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1488       if (1 > x->size[1] - 1) {
 1489         overflow = FALSE;
 1490       } else {
 1491         overflow = (x->size[1] - 1 > 2147483645);
 1492       }
 1493   
 1494       if (overflow) {
 1495         emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&jb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1496         check_forloop_overflow_error(TRUE);
 1497         emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&jb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1498       }
 1499   
 1500       emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&hb_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1501       for (k = 1; k <= x->size[1] - 1; k += 2) {
 1502         if ((x->data[k - 1] <= x->data[k]) || muDoubleScalarIsNaN(x->data[k])) {
 1503           overflow = TRUE;
 1504         } else {
 1505           overflow = FALSE;
 1506         }
 1507   
 1508         if (overflow) {
 1509         } else {
 1510           idx->data[k - 1] = k + 1;
 1511           idx->data[k] = k;
 1512         }
 1513       }
 1514   
 1515       emxInit_int32_T(&idx0, 1, &p_emlrtRTEI, TRUE);
 1516       k = idx0->size[0];
 1517       idx0->size[0] = x->size[1];
 1518       emxEnsureCapacity((emxArray__common *)idx0, k, (int32_T)sizeof(int32_T),
 1519                         &o_emlrtRTEI);
 1520       i = x->size[1];
 1521       for (k = 0; k < i; k++) {
 1522         idx0->data[k] = 1;
 1523       }
 1524   
 1525       i = 2;
 1526       while (i < x->size[1]) {
 1527         i2 = i << 1;
 1528         j = 1;
 1529         for (pEnd = 1 + i; pEnd < x->size[1] + 1; pEnd = qEnd + i) {
 1530           p = j;
 1531           q = pEnd - 1;
 1532           qEnd = j + i2;
 1533           if (qEnd > x->size[1] + 1) {
 1534             qEnd = x->size[1] + 1;
 1535           }
 1536   
 1537           k = 0;
 1538           kEnd = qEnd - j;
 1539           while (k + 1 <= kEnd) {
 1540             if ((x->data[idx->data[p - 1] - 1] <= x->data[idx->data[q] - 1]) ||
 1541                 muDoubleScalarIsNaN(x->data[idx->data[q] - 1])) {
 1542               overflow = TRUE;
 1543             } else {
 1544               overflow = FALSE;
 1545             }
 1546   
 1547             if (overflow) {
 1548               idx0->data[k] = idx->data[p - 1];
 1549               p++;
 1550               if (p == pEnd) {
 1551                 while (q + 1 < qEnd) {
 1552                   k++;
 1553                   idx0->data[k] = idx->data[q];
 1554                   q++;
 1555                 }
 1556               }
 1557             } else {
 1558               idx0->data[k] = idx->data[q];
 1559               q++;
 1560               if (q + 1 == qEnd) {
 1561                 while (p < pEnd) {
 1562                   k++;
 1563                   idx0->data[k] = idx->data[p - 1];
 1564                   p++;
 1565                 }
 1566               }
 1567             }
 1568   
 1569             k++;
 1570           }
 1571   
 1572           emlrtPushRtStackR2012b(&ib_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1573           emlrtPopRtStackR2012b(&ib_emlrtRSI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1574           for (k = 0; k + 1 <= kEnd; k++) {
 1575             idx->data[(j + k) - 1] = idx0->data[k];
 1576           }
 1577   
 1578           j = qEnd;
 1579         }
 1580   
 1581         i = i2;
 1582       }
 1583   
 1584       emxFree_int32_T(&idx0);
 1585     }
 1586   
 1587     emlrtHeapReferenceStackLeaveFcnR2012b(emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 1588   }

 1618   }

 3277           HbKernels[2].im = 0.0;

 3279           HbKernels[2].re = 0.0;
 3280           HbKernels[2].im = re / br;

 3283           HbKernels[2].im = re / br;
 3284         }
 3285       } else if (br == 0.0) {
 3286         if (epsc_re == 0.0) {
 3287           HbKernels[2].re = re / bi;
 3288           HbKernels[2].im = 0.0;
 3289         } else if (re == 0.0) {
 3290           HbKernels[2].re = 0.0;
 3291           HbKernels[2].im = -(epsc_re / bi);
 3292         } else {

 3294           HbKernels[2].im = -(epsc_re / bi);
 3295         }

 3299         if (brm > y) {
 3300           s = bi / br;

 3303           HbKernels[2].im = (re - s * epsc_re) / y;
 3304         } else if (y == brm) {
 3305           if (br > 0.0) {
 3306             y = 0.5;
 3307           } else {
 3308             y = -0.5;
 3309           }
 3310   
 3311           if (bi > 0.0) {
 3312             s = 0.5;
 3313           } else {
 3314             s = -0.5;
 3315           }

 3317           HbKernels[2].re = (epsc_re * y + re * s) / brm;
 3318           HbKernels[2].im = (re * y - epsc_re * s) / brm;
 3319         } else {
 3320           s = br / bi;
 3321           y = bi + s * br;
 3322           HbKernels[2].re = (s * epsc_re + re) / y;
 3323           HbKernels[2].im = (s * re - epsc_re) / y;
 3324         }
 3325       }

 3328       i4 = epsc->size[1];

 3336       epsc_re = epsc->data[1 + epsc->size[0] * ((int32_T)iTxLayer->data[0] - 1)].

 3339         epsc->data[1 + epsc->size[0] * ((int32_T)iTxLayer->data[0] - 1)].im;
 3340       y = epsc->data[1 + epsc->size[0] * ((int32_T)iTxLayer->data[0] - 1)].re *

 3342         epsc->data[1 + epsc->size[0] * ((int32_T)iTxLayer->data[0] - 1)].im *
 3343         epsc->data[1 + epsc->size[0] * ((int32_T)iTxLayer->data[0] - 1)].re;

 3345       ai = -muDoubleScalarPower(krho, 3.0) * gC_TM.im;

 3364           EzKernels[0].re = 0.0;

 3366         } else {

 3369         }
 3370       } else {
 3371         brm = muDoubleScalarAbs(br);

 3373         if (brm > y) {
 3374           s = bi / br;

 3380             y = 0.5;
 3381           } else {

 3383           }

 3399       }
 3400   
 3401       y = krho * krho * b_curlyRD.re;
 3402       re = krho * krho * b_curlyRD.im;
 3403       epsc_re = y * 0.0 - re;

 3406         iTxLayer->data[0] - 1)].re;

 3408         iTxLayer->data[0] - 1)].im;
 3409       if (bi == 0.0) {
 3410         if (re == 0.0) {

 3412           EzKernels[1].im = 0.0;

 3420       } else if (br == 0.0) {

 3438           EzKernels[1].im = (re - s * epsc_re) / y;

 3441             y = 0.5;
 3442           } else {
 3443             y = -0.5;
 3444           }
 3445

 3447             s = 0.5;
 3448           } else {
 3449             s = -0.5;
 3450           }
 3451   
 3452           EzKernels[1].re = (epsc_re * y + re * s) / brm;
 3453           EzKernels[1].im = (re * y - epsc_re * s) / brm;
 3454         } else {
 3455           s = br / bi;
 3456           y = bi + s * br;
 3457           EzKernels[1].re = (s * epsc_re + re) / y;

 3460       }
 3461   
 3462       /*  needs multiplication by 1i/omega/epsc(2,iTxLayer) after hankel  */
 3463       /*  transform (done here) */
 3464       /* Hz */
 3465       y = krho * krho * gA_TE_re;
 3466       re = krho * krho * gA_TE_im;
 3467       epsc_re = y * 0.0 - re;
 3468       re = y + re * 0.0;

 3479       }
 3480   
 3481       /*  needs multiplication by 1i/omega/mu after hankel  */
 3482       /*  transform (done here) */
 3483       /*  we're done now */
 3484     }
 3485   
 3486     emxFree_real_T(&iRxLayer);
 3487     emxFree_real_T(&iTxLayer);
 3488     emxFree_creal_T(&rTM);
 3489     emxFree_creal_T(&rTE);
 3490     emxFree_creal_T(&pzII);
 3491     emxFree_creal_T(&pzI);
 3492     emxFree_creal_T(&epsc);
 3493     emlrtHeapReferenceStackLeaveFcnR2012b(emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 3494   }

 3496   static void get_curly_R(const creal_T Rs_u, const creal_T Rs_d, const creal_T pz,
 3497     real_T zR, const emxArray_real_T *z, real_T iTxLayer, real_T omega, creal_T

 3499   {

 3501     int32_T i13;
 3502     int32_T i14;

 3553         im * pz.re);

 3556       im = omega * 2.0;
 3557       d_y.re = d * (re * pz.re - im * pz.im);
 3558       d_y.im = d * (re * pz.im + im * pz.re);
 3559       c_exp(&d_y);
 3560       re = 1.0 + (b_y.re * Rs_u.re - b_y.im * Rs_u.im);

 3562       r = y.re + (c_y.re * Rs_d.re - c_y.im * Rs_d.im);
 3563       b_r = y.im + (c_y.re * Rs_d.im + c_y.im * Rs_d.re);
 3564       b_re = re * r - im * b_r;

 3571         if (im == 0.0) {

 3591         }

 4180           finRB->re = (b_re + b_r * im) / r;
 4181           finRB->im = (im - b_r * b_re) / r;
 4182         } else if (r == re) {
 4183           if (c_r > 0.0) {
 4184             b_r = 0.5;
 4185           } else {
 4186             b_r = -0.5;
 4187           }
 4188   
 4189           if (d_r > 0.0) {
 4190             r = 0.5;
 4191           } else {
 4192             r = -0.5;
 4193           }
 4194   
 4195           finRB->re = (b_re * b_r + im * r) / re;
 4196           finRB->im = (im * b_r - b_re * r) / re;
 4197         } else {
 4198           b_r = c_r / d_r;
 4199           r = d_r + b_r * c_r;
 4200           finRB->re = (b_r * b_re + im) / r;
 4201           finRB->im = (b_r * im - b_re) / r;
 4202         }
 4203       }
 4204   
 4205       i12 = z->size[1];
 4206       i13 = (int32_T)(iTxLayer + 1.0);
 4207       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i13, 1, i12, &re_emlrtBCI,
 4208         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4209       re = omega * 0.0;
 4210       im = omega;
 4211       y.re = z->data[(int32_T)(iTxLayer + 1.0) - 1] * (2.0 * (re * pz.re - im *
 4212         pz.im));
 4213       y.im = z->data[(int32_T)(iTxLayer + 1.0) - 1] * (2.0 * (re * pz.im + im *
 4214         pz.re));
 4215       r = muDoubleScalarExp(y.re / 2.0);
 4216       re = omega * -0.0;
 4217       im = -omega;
 4218       b_y.im = zR * (re * pz.im + im * pz.re);
 4219       d_r = muDoubleScalarExp(zR * (re * pz.re - im * pz.im) / 2.0);
 4220       i12 = z->size[1];
 4221       i13 = (int32_T)iTxLayer;
 4222       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i13, 1, i12, &qe_emlrtBCI,
 4223         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4224       re = omega * -0.0;
 4225       im = -omega;
 4226       c_y.re = (2.0 * z->data[(int32_T)iTxLayer - 1] - zR) * (re * pz.re - im *
 4227         pz.im);
 4228       c_y.im = (2.0 * z->data[(int32_T)iTxLayer - 1] - zR) * (re * pz.im + im *
 4229         pz.re);
 4230       b_r = muDoubleScalarExp(c_y.re / 2.0);
 4231       re = omega * 0.0;
 4232       im = omega * 2.0;
 4233       d_y.im = d * (re * pz.im + im * pz.re);
 4234       c_r = muDoubleScalarExp(d * (re * pz.re - im * pz.im) / 2.0);
 4235       r_re = r * (r * muDoubleScalarCos(y.im));
 4236       r_im = r * (r * muDoubleScalarSin(y.im));
 4237       r = b_r * (b_r * muDoubleScalarCos(c_y.im));
 4238       b_r *= b_r * muDoubleScalarSin(c_y.im);
 4239       re = 1.0 + (r_re * -Rs_d.re - r_im * -Rs_d.im);
 4240       im = r_re * -Rs_d.im + r_im * -Rs_d.re;
 4241       r_re = d_r * (d_r * muDoubleScalarCos(b_y.im)) + (r * -Rs_u.re - b_r *
 4242         -Rs_u.im);
 4243       r_im = d_r * (d_r * muDoubleScalarSin(b_y.im)) + (r * -Rs_u.im + b_r *
 4244         -Rs_u.re);
 4245       b_re = re * r_re - im * r_im;
 4246       im = re * r_im + im * r_re;
 4247       r = Rs_u.re * Rs_d.re - Rs_u.im * Rs_d.im;
 4248       b_r = Rs_u.re * Rs_d.im + Rs_u.im * Rs_d.re;
 4249       r_re = c_r * (c_r * muDoubleScalarCos(d_y.im));
 4250       r_im = c_r * (c_r * muDoubleScalarSin(d_y.im));
 4251       c_r = 1.0 - (r * r_re - b_r * r_im);
 4252       d_r = 0.0 - (r * r_im + b_r * r_re);
 4253       if (d_r == 0.0) {
 4254         if (im == 0.0) {
 4255           finRC->re = b_re / c_r;
 4256           finRC->im = 0.0;
 4257         } else if (b_re == 0.0) {
 4258           finRC->re = 0.0;
 4259           finRC->im = im / c_r;
 4260         } else {
 4261           finRC->re = b_re / c_r;
 4262           finRC->im = im / c_r;
 4263         }
 4264       } else if (c_r == 0.0) {
 4265         if (b_re == 0.0) {
 4266           finRC->re = im / d_r;
 4267           finRC->im = 0.0;
 4268         } else if (im == 0.0) {
 4269           finRC->re = 0.0;
 4270           finRC->im = -(b_re / d_r);
 4271         } else {
 4272           finRC->re = im / d_r;
 4273           finRC->im = -(b_re / d_r);
 4274         }
 4275       } else {
 4276         re = muDoubleScalarAbs(c_r);
 4277         r = muDoubleScalarAbs(d_r);
 4278         if (re > r) {
 4279           b_r = d_r / c_r;
 4280           d = c_r + b_r * d_r;
 4281           finRC->re = (b_re + b_r * im) / d;
 4282           finRC->im = (im - b_r * b_re) / d;
 4283         } else if (r == re) {
 4284           if (c_r > 0.0) {
 4285             b_r = 0.5;
 4286           } else {
 4287             b_r = -0.5;
 4288           }
 4289   
 4290           if (d_r > 0.0) {
 4291             r = 0.5;
 4292           } else {
 4293             r = -0.5;
 4294           }
 4295   
 4296           finRC->re = (b_re * b_r + im * r) / re;
 4297           finRC->im = (im * b_r - b_re * r) / re;
 4298         } else {
 4299           b_r = c_r / d_r;
 4300           d = d_r + b_r * c_r;
 4301           finRC->re = (b_r * b_re + im) / d;
 4302           finRC->im = (b_r * im - b_re) / d;
 4303         }
 4304       }
 4305     }
 4306   }

 4309     *msgId, emxArray_creal_T *ret)

 4311     int32_T iv27[2];

 4313     int32_T i;

 4315     for (i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
 4316       iv27[i] = -1;
 4317       bv0[i] = TRUE;
 4318     }
 4319   
 4320     emlrtCheckVsBuiltInR2012b(emlrtRootTLSGlobal, msgId, src, "double", TRUE, 2U,
 4321       iv27, bv0, iv28);
 4322     i = ret->size[0] * ret->size[1];
 4323     ret->size[0] = iv28[0];
 4324     ret->size[1] = iv28[1];
 4325     emxEnsureCapacity((emxArray__common *)ret, i, (int32_T)sizeof(creal_T),
 4326                       (emlrtRTEInfo *)NULL);
 4327     emlrtImportArrayR2011b(src, ret->data, 8, TRUE);
 4328     emlrtDestroyArray(&src);
 4329   }

 4346   {

 4410       i9 = 0;

 4419         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);

 4426       emlrtRootTLSGlobal);

 4435   
 4436     emxInit_int32_T(&r25, 1, &gb_emlrtRTEI, TRUE);

 4438     r25->size[0] = i7 - i8;
 4439     emxEnsureCapacity((emxArray__common *)r25, i9, (int32_T)sizeof(int32_T),
 4440                       &gb_emlrtRTEI);
 4441     unnamed_idx_1 = i7 - i8;
 4442     for (i7 = 0; i7 < unnamed_idx_1; i7++) {

 4444     }

 4450

 4456     d->data[emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i9, 1, i7, &ne_emlrtBCI,
 4457       emlrtRootTLSGlobal) - 1] = 1.0;
 4458   
 4459     /*  Capital R is for a stack    */
 4460     /*  Starting from the bottom up, for Rs_down     */
 4461     Rlowerstack->re = 0.0;
 4462     Rlowerstack->im = 0.0;
 4463     i7 = (int32_T)-(iTxLayer + (-1.0 - ((real_T)z->size[1] - 1.0)));
 4464     emlrtForLoopVectorCheckR2012b((real_T)z->size[1] - 1.0, -1.0, iTxLayer,
 4465       mxDOUBLE_CLASS, i7, &vb_emlrtRTEI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4466     unnamed_idx_1 = 0;
 4467     while (unnamed_idx_1 <= i7 - 1) {
 4468       br = ((real_T)z->size[1] - 1.0) + -(real_T)unnamed_idx_1;
 4469       i9 = pz->size[1];
 4470       i8 = (int32_T)(br + 1.0);
 4471       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i8, 1, i9, &ke_emlrtBCI,
 4472         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4473       i9 = d->size[1];
 4474       i8 = (int32_T)(br + 1.0);
 4475       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i8, 1, i9, &he_emlrtBCI,
 4476         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4477       re = omega * 0.0;
 4478       im = omega * 2.0;
 4479       b_r = re * pz->data[(int32_T)(br + 1.0) - 1].re - im * pz->data[(int32_T)(br
 4480         + 1.0) - 1].im;
 4481       im = re * pz->data[(int32_T)(br + 1.0) - 1].im + im * pz->data[(int32_T)(br
 4482         + 1.0) - 1].re;
 4483       y_re = d->data[(int32_T)(br + 1.0) - 1] * b_r;
 4484       y_im = d->data[(int32_T)(br + 1.0) - 1] * im;
 4485       c_r = muDoubleScalarExp(y_re / 2.0);
 4486       i9 = r->size[1];
 4487       i8 = (int32_T)br;
 4488       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i8, 1, i9, &ge_emlrtBCI,
 4489         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4490       i9 = pz->size[1];
 4491       i8 = (int32_T)(br + 1.0);
 4492       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i8, 1, i9, &fe_emlrtBCI,
 4493         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4494       i9 = d->size[1];
 4495       i8 = (int32_T)(br + 1.0);
 4496       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i8, 1, i9, &ee_emlrtBCI,
 4497         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4498       re = omega * 0.0;
 4499       im = omega * 2.0;
 4500       b_r = re * pz->data[(int32_T)(br + 1.0) - 1].re - im * pz->data[(int32_T)(br
 4501         + 1.0) - 1].im;
 4502       im = re * pz->data[(int32_T)(br + 1.0) - 1].im + im * pz->data[(int32_T)(br
 4503         + 1.0) - 1].re;
 4504       y_re = d->data[(int32_T)(br + 1.0) - 1] * b_r;
 4505       re = d->data[(int32_T)(br + 1.0) - 1] * im;
 4506       b_r = muDoubleScalarExp(y_re / 2.0);
 4507       r_re = c_r * (c_r * muDoubleScalarCos(y_im));
 4508       c_r *= c_r * muDoubleScalarSin(y_im);
 4509       i9 = r->size[1];
 4510       i8 = (int32_T)br;
 4511       y_re = r->data[emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i8, 1, i9, &pe_emlrtBCI,
 4512         emlrtRootTLSGlobal) - 1].re + (Rlowerstack->re * r_re - Rlowerstack->im *
 4513         c_r);
 4514       i9 = r->size[1];
 4515       i8 = (int32_T)br;
 4516       y_im = r->data[emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i8, 1, i9, &pe_emlrtBCI,
 4517         emlrtRootTLSGlobal) - 1].im + (Rlowerstack->re * c_r + Rlowerstack->im *
 4518         r_re);
 4519       r_re = r->data[(int32_T)br - 1].re * Rlowerstack->re - r->data[(int32_T)br -
 4520         1].im * Rlowerstack->im;
 4521       c_r = r->data[(int32_T)br - 1].re * Rlowerstack->im + r->data[(int32_T)br -
 4522         1].im * Rlowerstack->re;
 4523       im = b_r * (b_r * muDoubleScalarCos(re));
 4524       re = b_r * (b_r * muDoubleScalarSin(re));
 4525       br = 1.0 + (r_re * im - c_r * re);
 4526       im = r_re * re + c_r * im;
 4527       if (im == 0.0) {
 4528         if (y_im == 0.0) {
 4529           Rlowerstack->re = y_re / br;
 4530           Rlowerstack->im = 0.0;
 4531         } else if (y_re == 0.0) {
 4532           Rlowerstack->re = 0.0;
 4533           Rlowerstack->im = y_im / br;
 4534         } else {
 4535           Rlowerstack->re = y_re / br;
 4536           Rlowerstack->im = y_im / br;
 4537         }
 4538       } else if (br == 0.0) {
 4539         if (y_re == 0.0) {
 4540           Rlowerstack->re = y_im / im;
 4541           Rlowerstack->im = 0.0;
 4542         } else if (y_im == 0.0) {
 4543           Rlowerstack->re = 0.0;
 4544           Rlowerstack->im = -(y_re / im);
 4545         } else {
 4546           Rlowerstack->re = y_im / im;
 4547           Rlowerstack->im = -(y_re / im);
 4548         }
 4549       } else {
 4550         c_r = muDoubleScalarAbs(br);
 4551         re = muDoubleScalarAbs(im);
 4552         if (c_r > re) {
 4553           b_r = im / br;
 4554           re = br + b_r * im;
 4555           Rlowerstack->re = (y_re + b_r * y_im) / re;
 4556           Rlowerstack->im = (y_im - b_r * y_re) / re;
 4557         } else if (re == c_r) {
 4558           if (br > 0.0) {
 4559             b_r = 0.5;
 4560           } else {
 4561             b_r = -0.5;
 4562           }
 4563   
 4564           if (im > 0.0) {
 4565             re = 0.5;
 4566           } else {
 4567             re = -0.5;
 4568           }
 4569   
 4570           Rlowerstack->re = (y_re * b_r + y_im * re) / c_r;
 4571           Rlowerstack->im = (y_im * b_r - y_re * re) / c_r;
 4572         } else {
 4573           b_r = br / im;
 4574           re = im + b_r * br;
 4575           Rlowerstack->re = (b_r * y_re + y_im) / re;
 4576           Rlowerstack->im = (b_r * y_im - y_re) / re;
 4577         }
 4578       }
 4579   
 4580       unnamed_idx_1++;
 4581       emlrtBreakCheckFastR2012b(emlrtBreakCheckR2012bFlagVar, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4582     }
 4583   
 4584     Rupperstack->re = 0.0;
 4585     Rupperstack->im = 0.0;
 4586   
 4587     /*  Starting from the top down for Rs_up */
 4588     emlrtForLoopVectorCheckR2012b(2.0, 1.0, iTxLayer, mxDOUBLE_CLASS, (int32_T)
 4589       (iTxLayer + -1.0), &ub_emlrtRTEI, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4590     unnamed_idx_1 = 0;
 4591     while (unnamed_idx_1 <= (int32_T)(iTxLayer + -1.0) - 1) {
 4592       i7 = pz->size[1];
 4593       i9 = (int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0);
 4594       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i9, 1, i7, &de_emlrtBCI,
 4595         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4596       i7 = d->size[1];
 4597       i9 = (int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0);
 4598       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i9, 1, i7, &ce_emlrtBCI,
 4599         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4600       re = omega * 0.0;
 4601       im = omega * 2.0;
 4602       b_r = re * pz->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1].re -
 4603         im * pz->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1].im;
 4604       im = re * pz->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1].im +
 4605         im * pz->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1].re;
 4606       y_re = d->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1] * b_r;
 4607       y_im = d->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1] * im;
 4608       c_r = muDoubleScalarExp(y_re / 2.0);
 4609       i7 = r->size[1];
 4610       i9 = (int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0);
 4611       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i9, 1, i7, &be_emlrtBCI,
 4612         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4613       i7 = pz->size[1];
 4614       i9 = (int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0);
 4615       emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i9, 1, i7, &ae_emlrtBCI,
 4616         emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4617       i7 = d->size[1];

 4626         im * pz->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1].re;
 4627       y_re = d->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1] * b_r;
 4628       re = d->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1] * im;

 4632       i7 = r->size[1];

 4634       y_re = -r->data[emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i9, 1, i7, &oe_emlrtBCI,

 4637       i7 = r->size[1];

 4639       y_im = -r->data[emlrtDynamicBoundsCheckFastR2012b(i9, 1, i7, &oe_emlrtBCI,

 4641         r_re);
 4642       r_re = r->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1].re *
 4643         Rupperstack->re - r->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) -
 4644         1].im * Rupperstack->im;
 4645       c_r = r->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) - 1].re *
 4646         Rupperstack->im + r->data[(int32_T)((2.0 + (real_T)unnamed_idx_1) - 1.0) -
 4647         1].im * Rupperstack->re;

 4649       re = b_r * (b_r * muDoubleScalarSin(re));
 4650       br = 1.0 - (r_re * im - c_r * re);
 4651       im = 0.0 - (r_re * re + c_r * im);
 4652       if (im == 0.0) {
 4653         if (y_im == 0.0) {
 4654           Rupperstack->re = y_re / br;
 4655           Rupperstack->im = 0.0;
 4656         } else if (y_re == 0.0) {
 4657           Rupperstack->re = 0.0;
 4658           Rupperstack->im = y_im / br;
 4659         } else {
 4660           Rupperstack->re = y_re / br;
 4661           Rupperstack->im = y_im / br;
 4662         }
 4663       } else if (br == 0.0) {
 4664         if (y_re == 0.0) {
 4665           Rupperstack->re = y_im / im;
 4666           Rupperstack->im = 0.0;
 4667         } else if (y_im == 0.0) {
 4668           Rupperstack->re = 0.0;
 4669           Rupperstack->im = -(y_re / im);
 4670         } else {
 4671           Rupperstack->re = y_im / im;
 4672           Rupperstack->im = -(y_re / im);
 4673         }
 4674       } else {
 4675         c_r = muDoubleScalarAbs(br);
 4676         re = muDoubleScalarAbs(im);
 4677         if (c_r > re) {
 4678           b_r = im / br;
 4679           re = br + b_r * im;
 4680           Rupperstack->re = (y_re + b_r * y_im) / re;
 4681           Rupperstack->im = (y_im - b_r * y_re) / re;
 4682         } else if (re == c_r) {
 4683           if (br > 0.0) {
 4684             b_r = 0.5;
 4685           } else {
 4686             b_r = -0.5;
 4687           }
 4688   
 4689           if (im > 0.0) {
 4690             re = 0.5;
 4691           } else {
 4692             re = -0.5;
 4693           }
 4694   
 4695           Rupperstack->re = (y_re * b_r + y_im * re) / c_r;
 4696           Rupperstack->im = (y_im * b_r - y_re * re) / c_r;
 4697         } else {
 4698           b_r = br / im;
 4699           re = im + b_r * br;
 4700           Rupperstack->re = (b_r * y_re + y_im) / re;
 4701           Rupperstack->im = (b_r * y_im - y_re) / re;
 4702         }
 4703       }
 4704   
 4705       unnamed_idx_1++;
 4706       emlrtBreakCheckFastR2012b(emlrtBreakCheckR2012bFlagVar, emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4707     }
 4708   
 4709     emxFree_real_T(&d);
 4710     emlrtHeapReferenceStackLeaveFcnR2012b(emlrtRootTLSGlobal);
 4711   }

 4967     /*  */
 4968     /*  Returns 1D CSEM fields due to an arbitrarily oriented electric dipole */
 4969     /*  */
 4970     /*  ***Bessel function integrals are evaluated using the digital filter */
 4971     /*     method (aka the Fast Hankel Transform) and lagged convolution*** */
 4972     /*   */
 4973     /*  In this code, I've only tested out the lagged convolution method which */
 4974     /*  requires that all receivers be at the same depth */
 4975     /*  */
 4976     /*  Returns the inline horizontal electric field from a frequency domain */
 4977     /*  horizontal electric dipole in an arbitrary N-layered medium.  */
 4978     /*  */
 4979     /*  Inputs: */
 4980     /*  */
 4981     /*  freqs  - Vector of frequencies (Hz)    */
 4982     /*  rRx    - Vector of ranges from transmitter to receivers (m, positive). */
 4983     /*  zRx    - Vector of depths of receivers (m), relative to where 0 is defined */
 4984     /*           in the model layer top-depths in z. */
 4985     /*  zTx    - Depth of transmitter (m) */
 4986     /*  z      - Layer top-depths (m). First value is ignored. Also 0 is anywhere  */
 4987     /*           you want it to be, this code makes no model assumptions other  */
 4988     /*           than that the values in z need to be increasing. */
 4989     /*  sig    - Conductivity of each layer (s/m).  z,sig need to include all */
 4990     /*           layers of the model. **This code makes no assumptions about air  */
 4991     /*           or sea layers.   */
 4992     /*  filterName     - Name of filter to use */
 4993     /*                  ('kk51Hankel.mat', 'kk101Hankel.mat', 'kk201Hankel.mat', , 'wa801Hankel.mat') */
 4994     /*  lUseLaggedConv - Optional. Set to true if you want to use the lagged */
 4995     /*                   convolution + spline interpolation speed up when computing */
 4996     /*                   response for many receivers. */
 4997     /*  RxAzim - Receiver azimuth from the dipole clockwise in degrees */
 4998     /*  */
 4999     /*  TxDip - Transmitter dip, +ve below horizontal in degrees */
 5000     /*  */
 5001     /*  */
 5002     /*  Note that the code currently requires both the transmitter and receiver */
 5003     /*  to be in the same layer. Also, if the transmitter and/or receiver are */
 5004     /*  positioned on a boundary, they are assumed to reside in the upper layer. */
 5005     /*  For example if they are on the seafloor, then the upper sea layer is */
 5006     /*  used. For land EM modeling, you should nudge the transmitter and */
 5007     /*  receiver a few cm into the earth (ie, zTx = 0.1 m), otherwise you'll be */
 5008     /*  telling the code to inject a 1 amp source current into the air, which i'm */
 5009     /*  told is quite difficult to do! */
 5010     /*   */
 5011     /*  Outputs: All components of the CSEM field due to an arbitrarilty oriented electric dipole,  */
 5012     /*  in cylindrical co-ordinates, as described in Lars Loseth's PhD thesis (2007)  */
 5013     /*  */
 5014     /*  */
 5015     /*  Written by: */
 5016     /*  */
 5017     /*  Kerry Key and Anandaroop Ray */
 5018     /*  Scripps Institution of Oceanography */
 5019     /*  */
 5020     /*  History: */
 5021     /*  */
 5022     /*  May 2011  - implemented */
 5023     /* -------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
 5024     if ((lUseLaggedConv == 1.0) && (rRx->size[1] == 1)) {
 5025       lUseLaggedConv = 0.0;
 5026     }

 5131     }

 5410     {

 5412       cst = csb;
 5413       apnd = B;

 5421       } else {

 5423       }

 5434       apnd = csb + ndbl * d;
 5435       if (d > 0.0) {
 5436         cdiff = apnd - B;
 5437       } else {
 5438         cdiff = B - apnd;
 5439       }

 5441       absa = muDoubleScalarAbs(csb);
 5442       lamMin = muDoubleScalarAbs(B);
 5443       if (absa > lamMin) {
 5444         b_absa = absa;
 5445       } else {
 5446         b_absa = lamMin;
 5447       }
 5448

 5450         ndbl++;
 5451         apnd = B;
 5452       } else if (cdiff > 0.0) {
 5453         apnd = csb + (ndbl - 1.0) * d;
 5454       } else {
 5455         ndbl++;
 5456       }
 5457   
 5458       n_too_large = (2.147483647E+9 < ndbl);

 5461       } else {

 5463       }
 5464     }
